Hlophe says this is “due to lack of insightful leadership and proper economic development projections.” His comments come as tensions remain high in the tiny country, with pro-democracy forces taking to the streets in protests and burning businesses as well as schools. Hlophe, from the Kunjalo Centre for Development Research, says King Mswati III will continue to run the country as if all is well because even the Southern African Development Community intervention is minimal on the matter. For more on this, here’s Hlophe...